The NotExceedsDocumentLengthTresholdDecideRule can not be used in the
scope rules as you have configured. Scope rules are applied prior to
any network activity and the size of the document is unknown at that
time. Only rules relating to the actual URL itself can be applied in
scope rules.&lt;br&gt;
  &lt;br&gt;
The NotExceedsDocumentLengthTresholdDecideRule should be used to
influence the behavior of processors. For each processor it is possible
to set a shouldProcessDecideRule attribute. If you merely wish to avoid
storing such long files, you could apply the filter to the
(W)ARCWriterProcessor.&lt;br&gt;
  &lt;br&gt;
If you wish to avoid downloading large files, you will need to apply
the setShouldFetchBodyRule to the FetchHTTP processor and make sure
your NotExceedsDocumentLengthTresholdDecideRule is set to use header
length. This will cause the FetchHTTP processor to run the decide rule
after fetching the HTTP header (which hopefully contains an accurate
content-length value) and will not download the actual file if it is
too large.&lt;br&gt;
